.TH "pci_release_regions" 9 "pci_release_regions" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pci_release_regions \- Release reserved PCI I/O and memory resources
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" pci_release_regions
.BI "(struct pci_dev *pdev "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pdev" 12
PCI device whose resources were previously reserved by
\fBpci_request_regions\fP
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Releases all PCI I/O and memory resources previously reserved by a
successful call to \fBpci_request_regions\fP.  Call this function only
after all use of the PCI regions has ceased.
